criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Controlled Systemic Alterial Hypertension

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Diabetes mellitus;

          -  heart failure;

          -  coronary artery disease;

          -  chronic renal failure;

          -  body mass index (BMI) ≥ 35 kg/m2;

          -  smokers;

          -  individuals with injuries to the upper and lower limbs that make the exercise protocol
             impossible;

          -  not using antihypertensive medication and using beta-blocker and/or alpha-blocker
             medication.
